    {
      "id": "head",
      "levels": [
        {"front": "head", "back": "la tête", "grammarNote": "To express pain in French, use 'avoir mal à + body part': j'ai mal à la tête (my head hurts), j'ai mal au dos (my back hurts), j'ai mal aux pieds (my feet hurt). The article contracts: à + le = au, à + les = aux."},
        {"front": "My head hurts.", "back": "J'ai mal à la tête."}
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "hair",
      "levels": [
        {"front": "hair", "back": "les cheveux (masc.)", "grammarNote": "'Les cheveux' is always plural in French (the collection of hair). One strand is 'un cheveu'. 'Elle a les cheveux longs' = She has long hair. Note: use the definite article with body parts, not possessives — 'elle a les cheveux courts', not 'ses cheveux courts'."},
        {"front": "She has long hair.", "back": "Elle a les cheveux longs."}
      ]
    },
    {
